{"title":"EB21: Pyga MoBu is a convertible carbon XC & Down Country MTB made in South Africa","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/03/eb21-pyga-mobu-is-a-convertible-carbon-xc-down-country-mtb-made-in-south-africa/","date":1630682332000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-270211\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>The Pyga MoBu is said to be the first full carbon mountain bike ever produced in South Africa. When Pyga founder, Patrick Morewood, set out to design to MoBu, his aim was to improve upon the Pyga Stage while future-proofing the frame. They’ve effectively ended up with two bikes that share the same frame; a 118mm travel XC/Marathon bike, and a 135mm travel Down Country Trail bike. We set eyes on it at EuroBike… here are the details.</p><h2>Pyga MoBu Carbon Mountain Bike</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:780x585/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" alt=\"pyga mobu 118mm travel xc marathon mtb full carbon south african\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1200\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa-297x223.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa-800x600.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa-120x90.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa-768x576.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa-1536x1152.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:780x585/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" ezoid=\"0.28252226357247445\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa-297x223.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa-800x600.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa-120x90.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa-768x576.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084405/pyga-mobu-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-made-in-south-africa-1536x1152.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1536w\"></a></p><p>The Pyga MoBu was shown in its shorter travel XC/Marathon build, running 118mm of rear wheel travel paired with a 120mm travel RockShox SID fork. This one runs a 185mm x 47.5mm shock, but switching to a longer stroke 185mm x 55mm shock increases the rear wheel travel to 135mm. That gives you the Down Country Trail configuration that pairs that additional rear travel with a 130mm travel fork. A lower shock mount flip-chip facilitates this change.</p><div id=\"attachment_270332\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-270332\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb.jpg\" alt=\"pyga mobu 439mm chainstatys full carbon mountain bike made in south africa\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1066\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb-1536x1023.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03084417/pyga-mobu-suspension-layout-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mtb-1536x1023.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-270332\">The Pyga MoBu runs a Horst-Link suspension platform; the rear triangle isn’t vertically braced, but there is some lateral bracing by nature of the fact that the chainstay is a one-piece design, with either side meeting at the main pivot recessed within the seat tube.</p></div><p>Though they use the exact same frame, the two bikes have slightly different geometries due to the longer travel fork on the Down County build. It has the slacker HA of 66.5° with a 76° effective seat tube angle. The shorter travel setup gets a 66° HA and 76.5° SA. A reach adjust headset gives riders the choice of running a 465mm or 480mm reach on the size large Down Country Trail build. On the XC/Marathon setup, the choice is between 474mm and 484mm.&nbsp;</p><p>The frame is designed around a 29″ wheelset, with chainstays measuring up at 439mm, consistent across the M-XL frame size range. Pyga reckon that caters to riders from 165cm to 195cm+.</p><div id=\"attachment_270344\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095507/pyga-mobu-xc-geometry-chart.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-270344\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095507/pyga-mobu-xc-geometry-chart.jpg\" alt=\"pyga mobu xc geometry\" width=\"1400\" height=\"705\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095507/pyga-mobu-xc-geometry-chart.jpg 1400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095507/pyga-mobu-xc-geometry-chart-297x150.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095507/pyga-mobu-xc-geometry-chart-800x403.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095507/pyga-mobu-xc-geometry-chart-120x60.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095507/pyga-mobu-xc-geometry-chart-768x387.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095507/pyga-mobu-xc-geometry-chart.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095507/pyga-mobu-xc-geometry-chart.jpg 1400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095507/pyga-mobu-xc-geometry-chart-297x150.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095507/pyga-mobu-xc-geometry-chart-800x403.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095507/pyga-mobu-xc-geometry-chart-120x60.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095507/pyga-mobu-xc-geometry-chart-768x387.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-270344\">Pyga MoBu XC/Marathon Geometry</p></div><div id=\"attachment_270343\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095504/pyga-mobu-downcountry-geometry.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-270343\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095504/pyga-mobu-downcountry-geometry.jpg\" alt=\"pyga mobu trail geometry\" width=\"1400\" height=\"704\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095504/pyga-mobu-downcountry-geometry.jpg 1400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095504/pyga-mobu-downcountry-geometry-297x149.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095504/pyga-mobu-downcountry-geometry-800x402.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095504/pyga-mobu-downcountry-geometry-120x60.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095504/pyga-mobu-downcountry-geometry-768x386.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095504/pyga-mobu-downcountry-geometry.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095504/pyga-mobu-downcountry-geometry.jpg 1400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095504/pyga-mobu-downcountry-geometry-297x149.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095504/pyga-mobu-downcountry-geometry-800x402.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095504/pyga-mobu-downcountry-geometry-120x60.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03095504/pyga-mobu-downcountry-geometry-768x386.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-270343\">Pyga MoBu Down Country Trail Geometry</p></div><h3>Made in South Africa</h3><div id=\"attachment_270350\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-270350\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset.jpg\" alt=\"pyga mobu frameset\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1017\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset-297x189.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset-800x509.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset-120x76.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset-768x488.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset-1536x976.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset-297x189.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset-800x509.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset-120x76.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset-768x488.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101907/pyga-mobu-135mm-travel-downcountry-29er-carbon-mtb-framset-1536x976.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-270350\">The name MoBu is derived from the Sesotho word meaning “soil” or “of the earth”</p></div><p><em>“Project MoBu is the realization of a dream to build the best carbon fiber mountain bikes in the world. In order to fulfill this dream, we needed to find a manufacturing partner who shared our passion for innovation and our belief that things can always be done better”</em> – Pyga Mountain Bikes. Luckily for them, they found that partner right on the doorstep in South Africa.</p><div id=\"attachment_270346\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-270346\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays.jpg\" alt=\"pyga mobu 148mm spacing\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1068\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03101644/pyga-mobu-148mm-spacing-439mm-chainstays-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-270346\">Like other Pyga frames before it, the MoBu runs a non-standard chainline whereby the cassette sits 2.5mm further out to the driveside</p></div><p>Blackstone Tek deal in the production of high-performance carbon fiber wheels and components for brands including Ducati, MV Agusta, Arch and others. In partnership with Pyga, they are manufacturing the MoBu using Toray-Mitsubishi T800 and T1100 fibers. Pyga say that, thanks to Blackstone Tek’s unique and proprietary manufacturing techniques, the resulting frame is “unparalleled in quality, strength and ride-ability”.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb.jpg\" alt=\"pyga slackline 160mm travel enduro mtb alluminium frame made in south africa\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1070\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb-297x199.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb-800x535.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb-768x514.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb-1536x1027.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb-297x199.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb-800x535.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb-768x514.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110303/pyga-slakline-160mm-travel-enduro-mtb-1536x1027.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p>Also on show at EuroBike were their aluminium full suspension mountain bikes that are also made in South Africa. We got eyes on the Pyga Slakline 160mm travel enduro bike, setup with a RockShox Super Deluxe Coil shock, Lyrik Ultimate fork and red anodised brakes, cockpit, pedals and drivetrain components from Hope Technology.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization.jpg\" alt=\"pyga sliver purple colorway alloy bike\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1069\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization-800x535.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization-1536x1026.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization-800x535.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03110835/pyga-silver-purple-retro-color-customization-1536x1026.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p>Showing off their ability to deliver a wide range of color customization for customers, Pyga brought along this 140mm travel Hyrax, duplicating the retro look of this Iron Horse from the 90s…</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple.jpg\" alt=\"iron horse downhill mtb 90s\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1070\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple-297x199.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple-800x535.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple-768x514.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple-1536x1027.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple-297x199.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple-800x535.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple-768x514.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03111328/retro-90s-mtb-iron-hose-downhill-bike-silver-purple-1536x1027.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>Pyga have the capacity to produce just 130 MoBu frames each year due to the low waste carbon production method employed by Blackstone Tek. They’ve already sold 30% of the bikes for this year and there’s already a 4 month waiting list. Which, actually, isn’t <em>that</em> long in the current climate. Join the waiting list now for around 5000€; that gets you the frame and a RockShox Super Deluxe Ultimate shock.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>The MoBu is available in the Raw Carbon colorway only, though there are 30 decal colors to choose from to match your fork, or not.</p><p><a href=\"https://eu.pygamountainbikes.com/?v=79cba1185463\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>PygaMountainBikes.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"baeeec2e8809be4c8ab50c3e80791e233b4c1b67d35131ef0ecb03c80ef534ed","category":"Cycling"}